gomodel:SYNGO_2031  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Background:\n- This paper studies glycinergic responses in motorneurons in the hypoglossal nucleus.\n- The spastic, spasmodic, and oscillator mice have mutations in resp. beta, alpha1 and alpha1 GlycR genes.\n- The spastic mouse have a non-coding mutation that expresses lower levels of the beta subunit.\n\nFig.2: \"Properties of glycinergic mIPSCs in control (spa/+) and spa/spa mice\"\nResults: \"the spastic mutation causes a dramatic reduction in mIPSC amplitude and frequency with no change in mIPSC kinetics\"\nDiscussion: \"Based on strychnine binding, the spastic mutation reduces GlyR numbers without altering affinity (supplemental Table 1, available at www.jneurosci.org as supplemental material) (White and Heller, 1982; Becker et al., 1986)\". Experimental description: \"Spastic, spasmodic, and oscillator mice were obtained from The Jackson Laboratory (Bar Harbor, ME)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2031" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

